{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fsr2","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/Scaling3DMode-swift.enum"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/Scaling3DMode-swift.enum\/fsr2","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/viewport\/scaling3dmode-swift.enum\/fsr2"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Use AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution 2.2 upscaling for the viewport’s 3D buffer. The amount of scaling can be set using ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Values less than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" will be result in the viewport being upscaled using FSR2. Values greater than "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are not supported and bilinear downsampling will be used instead. A value of "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will use FSR2 at native resolution as a TAA solution."}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"case","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fsr2","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Viewport.Scaling3DMode.fsr2","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot8ViewportC13Scaling3DModeO4fsr2yA2EmF","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Case","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/